      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0570P0-02222'>
        <a name='S5LV0570P0_19960306_GCR_167'>  </a>
        <blockquote class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <cite class='member author entry-title unmatched-member'>The Earl of Lindsay</cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            As my noble friend well knows, deer numbers in Scotland are 600,000 or so, rising fast, and the deer range is reducing. Deer management is needed, and it may be that where emergency circumstances justify it, moving deer with the use of vehicles for management purposes could be justified. It would be subject to the various codes of practice.</p><p>
            The effect of Amendment No. 65 would be to allow the movement of deer with the use of vehicles simply for sporting purposes. The Government do not believe that vehicles should be used to move deer for sporting purposes. That would be the effect of Amendment No. 65 and that is why we oppose it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0570P0-02223'>
