        <q>and the natural beauty and amenity of the countryside",</q>
        from the definition of natural heritage which is to be found in Clause 9 of the Bill. The definition at the moment reads:
        <q>'natural heritage' includes flora and fauna, geological and physiographical features and the natural beauty and amenity of the countryside".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0570P0-02295'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0570P0_19960306_GCR_240' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
